{
  "doc_id": "4218",
  "text": "Overt attentional responses are often accompanied by measurable autonomic changes. For example, infant attention to visual and auditory stimuli is accompanied by decreases in heart rate [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Moreover, heightened infant attention is associated with reductions in heart rate variability [CITATION_3] . One would expect similar links between other overt behaviours and autonomic measures.",
